  "text": "DBT cells were cotransfected with pSFssS2 together with either pSFSlutt or pSFSltmd and the expressed proteins were analysed by Western blotting. As shown in Fig. 3 , there was no substantial difference in the size of S 1 and $2 proteins when they were expressed individually or simultaneously. However, the amount of Slutt protein expressed by itself (Fig. 2a, lane 3) was significantly lower than when expressed together with the ssS2 protein (Fig. 3a, lane 2) . This suggests that most of the Slutt protein synthesized was excreted from the cells, since the S lutt protein lacked a transmembrane domain. The large amounts of S lutt protein detected in cells when expressed together with the ssS2 protein could be explained by the association of the Slutt and ssS2 proteins, which is similar to the association of the S1 and $2 proteins detected in cells infected with cl-2 [CITATION_1] .",
